HEADWORD: conessi
<hw>conessi</hw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>a tropical Asian tree
(<spn>Holarrhena pubescens</spn> or <spn>Holarrhena
antidysenterica</spn>) with hard white wood and bark formerly used as a
remedy for dysentery and diarrhea.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ivory tree, kurchi, kurchee, <spn>Holarrhena
pubescens</spn>, <spn>Holarrhena antidysenterica</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

